@cpmeister hmm, these two new classes are trivial inherited classes from the base handler class; so if I add @NonNullByDefault to them, it causes an mvn build error by differing from the parent class.
To correct the mvn build errors, I would need to add @NonNullByDefault to the parent base class. Which means I would have to do the same to the other classes derived from the base. And I suspect this would cause a full rat's tail of null analysis changes to many other classes in the binding.
So, in fact I would prefer to follow your prior suggestion, and defer ALL of the null annotation changes to a separate PR. => Is that OK with you?
